buttons.title: Magnolia champaca (L.) Figlar - National Parks Board (NParks)
buttons.snippet: Leaf is elliptic or narrowly ovate (10 – 35 cm long by 4 – 11 cm wide), spirally arranged and slightly hairy on the underside. Leaf tip is short while leaf base is cuneate to rounded. There are 14 – 23 pairs of secondary veins which can be seen more visibly on the underside of the leaf. Petiole 1.5-3.5 (4) cm long.
